    "(3)In detail,T 2 ( z, z) ∈ R | I|≥0 contains a sequence of Mahalanobis distances, computed for each observation in z with respect to the benchmark dataset z. III.",
    "Consider a process modelled as a discrete-time system S, with sampling time τ, S:x p (k + 1) = f p x p (k), u(k) y p (k) = g p x p (k), u(k),(4)with f p and g p generic functions, x p ∈ R nx p, u ∈ R nu, and y p ∈ R ny the state, input, and output vectors of the process, respectively, and k a discrete-time counter for time steps of length τ.",
    "Specifically, the input u = ũ⊤ d ⊤ ⊤ includes all exogenous signals acting on S, i.e., manipulated control variables ũ ∈ R nũ and external disturbances d ∈ R n d, which are assumed to be measurable and predictable.",
    "The system is assumed to operate under multiple conditions, each characterized by distinct datasets representing system behaviour in those conditions.",
    "A typical example can be observed in energy systems, where load demand shifts between seasonal operating ranges, such as transitioning from summer to winter conditions."
